now blowers 119.4 cm and 137.2 cm (47 in. and 54 in.)<\/div><\/li><li><div>Rotary tillers (647)<\/div><\/li><\/ul><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Yanmar is a U.S.-registered trademark of Yanmar Company Limited.<\/p>","TitleQuestion":"Powerful Tier 4-compliant diesel engine and standard dual mid-selective control valve (SCV)"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>Both 4WD and power steering are standard equipment on the 1025R. This combination allows for excellent maneuverability and ease of operation of the tractor.<\/p><ul><li>Narrow overall width allows the&nbsp;1025R to work in tight areas where most compact tractors just cannot fit, yet&nbsp;the&nbsp;144.8-cm (57-in.) wheel base and 119.4 cm (47 in.) overall width gives great stability for all type of terrains.<\/li><li>Power steering means fewer turns of the steering wheel than manual steering; especially valuable when mowing around obstacles or when the tractor is used with a front loader.<\/li><li>High horsepower-to-weight ratio makes the 1025R a good choice for a variety of tasks; overall tractor weight reduces ground compaction and makes the 1025R an excellent mowing tractor.<\/li><li>The power take-off (PTO) is a fully-independent PTO on the 1025R, allowing engaging and disengaging of the PTO without stopping tractor movement. This is important when driving across obstacles such as driveways while mowing.<\/li><\/ul>","TitleQuestion":"Easy operation four-wheel drive (4WD) power steering"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><ul><li>Front Quik-Tatch&trade;&nbsp;hitch makes changing front implements quick and easy<\/li><li>All front implements (blade, brooms, and snow blowers) use a common hitch<\/li><li>AutoConnect&trade; mid-mount mower decks,&nbsp;D120 and H120&nbsp;Loaders, and 260 Backhoe&nbsp;can be taken on or off within&nbsp;5 minutes, and no tools are necessary<\/li><li>Changing rear implements is&nbsp;a snap with the iMatch<sup><small>TM<\/small><\/sup>&nbsp;Quick-Hitch, which has three fixed points to back in and pick up a rear implement that is&nbsp;iMatch compatible<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>*Features shown are available with all current model year tractors.<\/p>","TitleQuestion":"Fast and easy implement changeover"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/1023e_1026r_cuts/r4g032161_implement_compounding.jpg\" alt=\"Implement compounding (1025R Tractor shown)\" /><span class=\"caption\">Implement compounding (1025R Tractor shown)<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><ul class=\"noindent\"><li>Allows mounting more than one implement at a time, eliminating implement changeover<\/li><li>Loader, mid mower, backhoe,&nbsp;and a variety of 3-point hitch implements can be attached to the tractor at the same time<\/li><\/ul>","TitleQuestion":"Implement compounding improves efficiency"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>The&nbsp;1023E and 1025R Tractors feature a HST.<\/p><ul><li>Fluid under pressure transmits engine power to the drive wheels through a hydraulic pump and motor<\/li><li>The hydrostatic-drive unit functions both as a clutch and transmission<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/1023e_1026r_cuts/r4b000883_11_twin-touch_ctrls_1026r.jpg\" alt=\"Twin Touch foot controls \" /><span class=\"caption\">Twin Touch foot controls <\/span><\/div><\/div><p>Twin Touch&nbsp;foot controls allow selecting both speed and direction of travel with a touch of the toe. Ideally suited for jobs where productivity is a must, such as loader or mower applications.<\/p><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><ul><li>Infinite ground speeds, even at full throttle, to match the job<\/li><li>No clutching for fast direction changes<\/li><li>Faster, easier, and more precise to operate than competitive tractors with treadle pedal design (toe-heel)<\/li><li>Provides high torque for start up<\/li><li>Reduces power train shock loads<\/li><li>Large foot pedals were designed for operator comfort and allow for convenient operation of the tractor<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/1023e_1026r_cuts/r4g033107_2_speed_transmission.jpg\" alt=\"Two-speed transmission\" /><span class=\"caption\">Two-speed transmission<\/span><\/div><\/div><p>Transmission has two speeds - Hi and Lo range.<\/p><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><ul><li>The range lever is located next to the seat, conveniently within reach of the operator<\/li><li>Lo range allows performing tougher tasks at higher speeds than competitive tractors equipped with a three-range transmission (that is, lo range on three-speed transaxle is slower than lo range on a two-speed transaxle)<\/li><\/ul><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Durability features include:<\/p><ol><li>Large forged one-piece trunnion shaft with larger support bearings that reduce vibration and noise.<\/li><li>Innovative transaxle combines an HST, gear reduction axle, and clutch.<\/li><li>Pressure side filtration allows using a finer-mesh filter (10 micron) than suction filtration systems use on many competitive tractors.<\/li><li>One pump to supply charge pressure and implement flow. A flow divider splits the flow to various circuits throughout the tractor.<\/li><li>The transaxle has an oil cooler which provides improved hydraulic cooling performance.<\/li><\/ol>","TitleQuestion":"Hydrostatic transmission (HST) with Twin Touch&trade; foot controls"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/1023e_1026r_cuts/r4g031968_open_op_station.jpg\" alt=\"Open operator\'s station\" /><span class=\"caption\">Open operator\'s station<\/span><\/div><\/div><p>The&nbsp;1025R operator\'s station has been designed to allow greater operator comfort and increased visibility. Large and easy to grab handrails are located on each fender for an easier on and off of the tractor from either side.<\/p><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><ul><li>Sloping hood design provides improved visibility<\/li><li>Operator\'s station provides plenty of room for comfortable operation<\/li><li>Step-through textured flat operator station makes getting on and off the tractor easy from either side of the tractor&nbsp;<\/li><li>Fender-mounted handrails are large and easy to grab; located on each fender, they assist the operator in getting on and off the tractor<\/li><li>Controls are located next to the fenders for operator convenience<\/li><li>Operator controls are color-coded for easy identification of operation<\/li><li>Front-horizontal exhaust for increased operator visibility<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>*Features shown are available with all current model year tractors.<\/p><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/1023e_1026r_cuts/r4b000870_11_op_presence_syst_1026r.jpg\" alt=\"Operator presence system\" /><span class=\"caption\">Operator presence system<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><ul><li>If the operator leaves the tractor seat when the transmission, mid or rear power take-off (PTO) is engaged, the engine will shut down<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/1023e_1026r_cuts/r4b000897_11_rops_1026r.jpg\" alt=\"Foldable Roll-Gard ROPS \" /><span class=\"caption\">Foldable Roll-Gard ROPS <\/span><\/div><\/div><p>Foldable Roll-Gard&trade;&nbsp;rollover protective structure (ROPS)&nbsp;and retractable-seat belt are standard equipment to protect the operator in the event of a tractor tip-over, as well as&nbsp;improve the ability to store tractor in a garage.<\/p><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>Seat belt is within easy reach of the operator, to encourage the use of it whenever operating the tractor.<\/p><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>*Features shown are available with all current model year tractors<\/p><h5>Lighting<\/h5><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/1023e_1026r_cuts/r4b000782_11_lighting_1026r.jpg\" alt=\"Standard (and optional) lighting shown\" /><span class=\"caption\">Standard (and optional) lighting shown<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>Standard equipment lighting includes:<\/p><ul><li><div>Two front-mounted sealed-beam halogen headlights<\/div><\/li><li><div>Two amber-flashing warning/hazard lights mounted on the side of the ROPS with reflectors<\/div><\/li><li><div>Two additional fender lights are standard on the 1025R<\/div><\/li><li>Additional front- and rear-light kits are available<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>*Features shown are available with all current model year tractors<\/p>","TitleQuestion":"Open operator\'s station is comfortable and convenient"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/imatch_hitch/imatch_quick-hitch.jpg\" alt=\"iMatch Quick-Hitch\" /><span class=\"caption\">iMatch Quick-Hitch<\/span><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/imatch_hitch/imatch_quick-hitch_coupled.jpg\" alt=\"iMatch Quick-Hitch with rotary cutter hookup\" /><span class=\"caption\">iMatch Quick-Hitch with rotary cutter hookup<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/3e_series/r4a021811_quick_hitch.jpg\" alt=\"iMatch Quick-Hitch (LVB25976)\" /><span class=\"caption\">iMatch Quick-Hitch (LVB25976)<\/span><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/features_attachment/3e_series/r4a021752_rotary_cutter.jpg\" alt=\"iMatch Quick-Hitch with rotary cutter hookup (LVB25976)\" /><span class=\"caption\">iMatch Quick-Hitch with rotary cutter hookup (LVB25976)<\/span><\/div><\/div><p>One of the greatest&nbsp;operator concerns involves difficulty in attaching tractor implements. John Deere has addressed this issue with the iMatch Quick-Hitch.<\/p><p>The iMatch Quick-Hitch provides easy hookup and a guaranteed fit for all Category 1 implements that are designed to meet the American Society of Agricultural and Biological Engineers (ASABE) Category 1 Standard S278.6 for quick-attach hitches.<\/p><ul><li>All implements require a set of bushings in order for the attachment to fit and work properly with the iMatch Quick-Hitch. One set of bushings comes with the iMatch Quick-Hitch.<\/li><\/ul><p><em>NOTE: The bushing set can be seen in the picture above. These bushings allow the hooks on the iMatch and the pins on the implement to fit together properly. All other implements (box blades, tillers, rear blades, etc.) will require a set of bushings to enlarge the pin to fit with the iMatch hooks. Bushings of different lengths can be found in the parts system or through a bushing supplier (see dimensions below).<\/em><\/p><ul><li>Upper bushing<ul><li>Inside diameter: 1.93-1.95 cm (0.76-0.77 in.)<\/li><li>Outside diameter: 3.15-3.18 cm (1.24-1.25 in.)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Lower bushings<ul><li>Inside diameter: 2.24-2.26 cm (0.88 to 0.89 in.)<\/li><li>Outside diameter: 3.63-3.66 cm (1.43 to 1.44 in.)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>","TitleQuestion":"Optional iMatch&trade; Quick-Hitch feature allows for easy implement hookup"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1023e_gas_lift_spring.jpg\" alt=\"Gas-lift spring\" /><span class=\"caption\">Gas-lift spring<\/span><\/div><\/div><ul><li>The under-hood gas-lift support provides easy one-finger access to the engine compartment and eliminates the need for a mechanical prop rod.<\/li><li>This design of the support structure provides excellent rigidity for the hood.<\/li><\/ul>","TitleQuestion":"Easy-open, gas-lift hood"},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_tractor.jpg\" alt=\"1025R Tractor\" /><span class=\"caption\">1025R Tractor<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><ul><li>The 1 Family tractors includes factory-installed mechanical deck lift components.<\/li><li>The addition of these components from the factory significantly reduces the time required to do the initial mower deck installation at the time of purchase.<\/li><li>Refer to the mowers and material collection page for more details on mower deck installation and compatibility.<\/li><\/ul>","TitleQuestion":"Mower deck lift components "},{"Description":"<div class=\"seccion-images\"><\/div><p>The cab offers protection from the elements and expands the versatility of 1025R Tractors to perform in all climates.<\/p><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_1.jpg\" alt=\"1025R Cab \u2013 LP68087\" /><span class=\"caption\">1025R Cab \u2013 LP68087<\/span><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/clearpix.gif\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><\/div><p><strong>Key features<\/strong>:<\/p><ul><li>Full glass doors for maximum visibility<ul><li>Curved glass for a styled look<\/li><li>Sealed for cold weather operation<\/li><li>Easily removable for summer operation<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Heater with fan<ul><li>Switches and vents integrated into headliner<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Dome light<\/li><li>Fully openable front and rear windows with gas struts<\/li><li>Front sun visor<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_2.jpg\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/clearpix.gif\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><\/div><ul><li>Front work lights<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_3.jpg\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/clearpix.gif\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><\/div><ul><li>Front wiper with washer system<\/li><li>Dual outside mirrors<\/li><li>Rollover protective structure (ROPS) certified cab frame<ul><li>Allows for improved rear visibility<\/li><li>Reduces overall height<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Rubber isolation at all mounting points<\/li><li>Interior sound insulation<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_4.jpg\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/clearpix.gif\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><\/div><ul><li>Immersion-primed and powder-coated cab frame<ul><li>Provides superior corrosion resistance<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Integrated John Deere styling<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_5.jpg\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/clearpix.gif\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><\/div><p><strong>Specifications:<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Cab height: 1525 mm (60 in.)<\/li><li>Overall height when installed: 1990 mm (78.4 in.)<\/li><li>Overall height when installed to top of beacon: 2159 mm (85 in.)<\/li><li>Overall width with cab installed: same as tractor width<\/li><li>Cab weight: 200 kg (440 lb)<\/li><\/ul><div class=\"seccion-images\"><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_6.jpg\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_7.jpg\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><div><img src=\"http://salesmanual.deere.com/sales/salesmanual/images/NA/tractors/cuts/1025r_opt_cab_8.jpg\" alt=\"#\" /><\/div><\/div><p><strong>Optional kits:<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Rear wiper kit &ndash; BLV11241<\/li><li>Stereo kit &ndash; LVB26198<\/li><li>Radio (AM/FM, weatherband, SIRIUS&reg; Satellite, and iPod&reg; ready<em>) <\/em>- SWJHD1630<\/li><li>Beacon light kit &ndash; BLV11024<\/li><li>Light-emitting diode (LED) rear work light kit &ndash; BLV11244<\/li><li>Illuminated license plate kit &ndash; BLV11246<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Compatibility and Installation:<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Not compatible with:<ul><li>1023E<\/li><li>1025R TLB (FILB)<\/li><li>1026R TLB (FILB)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Compatible with all tractor implements except 260 Backhoe.<\/li><\/ul><p>&nbsp;<\/p><p>SIRIUS is a trademark of Sirius XM Radio, Inc. iPod is a trademark of Apple Inc.<\/p>","TitleQuestion":"Optional cab offers protection from elements"}],"SubTitle":null}},"ComponentInvisible":null,"Name":"Expand-Collapse Features"},"ID":"1548198808753","ModifiedDate":"October 10,2019 09:22:20 Central Daylight Time","MetaData":{"Title":"1025R Tractor | Sub-Compact Tractors | John Deere US","Description":"1 Family Sub-Compact Tractors, 1 Family 1025R","Keywords":"Tractors, 1025R Sub-Compact Tractors, 1025R, Tractors,  Sub-Compacts"}}}';

